What would you change to make you recons:
Increase withholding for Social Security and Medicare by a small amount. It has not been raised in years, while cost continue to go up every year.   Increase the ceiling on the Social security deductions as well.
For food programs limit the food choices for Snap benefits. Foods like chips, twinkies, energy drinks and pop should not be allowed to be purchased with SNAP benefits. I worked in retail food for about 15 years and watched as people who could least afford junk food buy only those things quite often. Eating such foods contributes to obesity, illness and poor outcomes, especially for children. It also does not teach them how to eat properly.  Part of the program should include meal planning and healthy food choices. Also should include safe handling of food. I am also a landlord and have had people call about getting sick because refrigerator was not keeping food cold. When we went down to see what the issue was, we almost always found food, meats and dairy on the counter, and warm.  This is basic knowledge that many do not know. Perhaps a good school class to be taught to young people about food safety, nutrition and good foods to feel your best. Also where the food comes from.  All recipients of SNAP benefits should be required to take a nutrition class, food prep, and safe food handling and storage.
Medicine is far too expensive and need to be regulated.  The current model of Doctor care for patients is not acceptable. A few minutes with a patient and lot of tests and money later with no good results for patients. A trial and error approach using the latest pharmaceutical is not the best way to heal. No way can anyone get to the real source of the problems so actual healing can take place.  Drugs cannot help either without good direction given the time most Docs spend with patients.  
Energy seems to be an all or nothing approach at this point. We do need to update transmission lines to facilitate an ever broadening need for energy. Likewise we need to use both clean energy and fossil fuels at this point in order to satisfy those needs. I have heard about Spain and their power shut down with just green energy. France came to their rescue with nuclear energy.  I do not want to see our country in the same position as Spain with just clean energy.  We should think about adding nuclear power to our energy portfolio if we are serious about slowly utilizing less fossil fuels.
I would like to see a much simplified tax system that is more fair to everyone at all income levels.  People at really high income levels should expect to pay more in taxes.
Education is so expensive. I would like to see higher education move to more trade schools and maybe even more classes that kids in the last two years of high school can take for a more promising future of employment with decent pay and benefits.
Overall with some work your plan could be much better for everyone, because clearly what we are doing now is not working for everyone, and sometimes not for anyone. While I feel we are once again headed in the right direction in some areas, there certainly is need for more work to be done.
